body:
Here are some ideas I've been thinking about when I walk through the wizard. I think you could get some pretty good bang for the buck on adding some options to the project creation process.  They may have been mentioned somewhere already.

I would suggest adding the creation options to the flutter creation wizard. I would add a few more too. 

![screen shot 2017-05-21 at 12 20 38 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1326504/26286808/8bab0656-3e22-11e7-8861-a96a53d00793.png)

comment_data.body: Somewhat related to #535 (wrt to a flow for accessing examples).

Adding one more idea. I've seen discussion on this around too. 

The android package name, it would be quite nice to set this up in the beginning.

![screen shot 2017-05-22 at 6 51 08 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1326504/26312171/9c2ce76c-3ebb-11e7-88f8-dcc9d1c89c47.png)

The position may not be ideal, b/c maybe it should go after the type of project is selected, because a plugin project could use it too. ...
This is landed.  Feel free to re-open for refinements.  Thanks again @branflake2267 !

milestone.description: Work triaged but not yet planned for a specific release.

title: Some ideas on project creation
